    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - IN-CHASSIS PROCEDURES - Branch Tube Assembly</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Branch Tube Assembly</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="11">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <revend/>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, make sure the engine has cooled before removing
                        components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not let engine fluids stay on your skin. Clean skin
                        and nails using hand cleaner and wash with soap and water. Wash or discard clothing and rags
                        contaminated with engine fluids.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <note>
                    <para>Engine fluids (oil, fuel, and coolant) are a threat to the environment. Recycle or dispose of
                        engine fluids according to local regulations. Never put engine fluids in the trash, pour fluids
                        on the ground, in sewers or bodies of water.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, always disconnect main negative battery cable first.
                        Always connect the main negative battery cable last.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect negative battery cable and Electronic Control Module (ECM) ground.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain air tanks, if equipped.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove inside engine cover from truck, if equipped. See Truck Service Manual.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the right inner fender well, if required.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic20" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D31515.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="360px"/>
                <caption>Parts for removal (Engine In-chassis - 4100 truck)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air intake duct</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air compressor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger air inlet duct</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Charge Air Cooler (CAC) pipe</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air conditioning compressor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Serpentine drive belt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Belt tensioner</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Alternator assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air filter housing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust down pipe</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger exhaust clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Shielded tube exhaust assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air intake duct, air filter housing, and mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen CAC pipe clamps and remove CAC pipe.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate belt tensioner clockwise to release belt tension and remove serpentine drive
                    belts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove alternator wiring and remove alternator assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not open pressurized air conditioning lines.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If truck is equipped with air conditioning, remove air conditioning compressor bolts
                    from mounting bracket, but do not remove or disconnect pressurized air conditioning lines. Move
                    compressor out of the way and secure with a strap.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting bracket for alternator and air conditioning compressor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If truck is equipped with an air compressor, remove coolant supply line and pinch off
                    hose. Remove two of three M10 air compressor mounting bracket bolts. Loosen third bolt and pivot or
                    reposition air compressor out of the way.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required to remove valve covers; remove oil dipstick, washer bottle, and bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen turbocharger exhaust clamp and remove exhaust down pipe from turbocharger exhaust
                    flange.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic01" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D31507.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"/>
                <caption>Parts for removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger air inlet duct</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Glow plug relay</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger exhaust flange</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear engine mounting bracket (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">V-clamp (Right exhaust tube to EGR cooler)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pump gasket heat shield</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear cover</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">V-clamp (Shielded tube exhaust assembly to turbocharger)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Electronic Control Module (ECM) / Injector Drive Module (IDM)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EGR Drive Module</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen V-clamp connecting shielded tube exhaust assembly to turbocharger.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen V-clamp connecting right exhaust tube to EGR cooler.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic02" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D31508.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"/>
                <caption>Air Management System parts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Shielded tube exhaust assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger exhaust flange</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust tube assembly, right</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust manifold, right</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">V-clamp (Shielded tube exhaust assembly to turbocharger)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pump gasket heat shield</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust manifold, left</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two M8 bolts and nuts connecting shielded tube exhaust assembly to left exhaust
                    manifold.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two M8 bolts and nuts connecting right exhaust tube to right exhaust manifold.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Leaving right exhaust tube attached, remove shielded tube exhaust assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove three bolts from pump gasket heat shield and remove heat shield.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unplug the EGR drive module and remove module and mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unplug ECM and IDM electrical connectors.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">See Engine Service Manual - "Engine Electrical" to remove the following:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>ECM, IDM, and mounting bracket.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Glow plug relay and bracket</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">See Engine Service Manual - "Electronically Controlled Variable Geometry Turbocharger
                    (VGT)" to remove the following:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Turbocharger air inlet duct</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>VGT assembly</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the high-pressure oil pump cover. See Engine Service Manual - "High-pressure Oil
                    Pump".
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">See Engine Service Manual - "Cylinder Head and Valve Train" to remove the following:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Valve covers</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>High-pressure oil rails</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Case-to-head tube assemblies</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Fuel injectors for cylinders 6, 7, and 8.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Rocker arm assemblies (intake and exhaust) for cylinders 7 and 8.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Rocker arm assembly (exhaust) for cylinder 6.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a suitable lifting device to support and lower
                        transmission assembly.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove transmission assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove clutch assembly, if equipped with a manual transmission.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">See Engine Service Manual - "Rear Cover, Flywheel, and Power Steering Gear Drive" to
                    remove the following:
                </para>
            </step1>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Flywheel or flex-plate</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Oil seal carrier</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Power steering idler gear</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Crankshaft secondary flange</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two M10 x 30 bolts from power steering and fuel pump assembly, and support the
                    power steering and fuel pump assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect starter motor assembly wiring, remove M10 bolts from starter motor, and
                    remove starter motor assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic03" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD16/D1615.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Removal of through bolt from rear engine mount in chassis mounting bracket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear engine mounting bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Chassis mounting bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Through bolt</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a chain hoist rated for the weight of the engine,
                        follow manufacturer's installation and safety instructions, and attach safety latch lifting
                        hooks to lifting eyes on the engine.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a hoist to support the engine.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two M16 through bolts and nuts from rear engine mounts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise engine with a hoist and support engine with a jack.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove eight M12 bolts from rear engine mounting brackets, and remove brackets from rear
                    cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove wiring retaining clips from rear cover assembly, if installed.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic04" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD06/D06150.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="1"/>
                <caption>Rear cover mounting bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts marked A, (M10 x 55) (5)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts marked B, (M10 x 70) (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts marked C, (M10 x 60) (4)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove rear cover mounting bolts marked A and C in figure.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a suitable lifting device or get help to lower rear
                        cover.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen rear cover mounting bolts marked B, but do not remove.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage when removing the rear cover, avoid pulling out gasket between the
                        upper and lower crankcase.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a thin gasket scraper to separate sealant between the upper and lower crankcase and
                    the rear cover assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove rear cover mounting bolts marked B and remove rear cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic05" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD06/D0636.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Sealant at upper and lower crankcase</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, cut sealant at upper and lower crankcase.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove remaining sealant from upper crankcase, lower crankcase and rear cover, using a
                    sharp gasket scraper or putty knife.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove intake and exhaust pushrods from cylinders 7 and 8.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove exhaust pushrod from cylinder 6.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a No. 27 torx bit to a 1/4 x 10 inch extension.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic06" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD13/D13131.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Extension in pushrod hole</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Look through back of crankcase and insert extension through exhaust pushrod hole for
                    cylinder 6 and push torx bit into M6 x 40 torx bolt in block of branch tube assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not drop mounting bolts into crankcase.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully loosen torx bolt to allow removal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove extension from pushrod hole.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Look through back of crankcase and use a magnet to carefully remove torx bolt in one of
                    three ways:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Magnet inserted through pushrod hole</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Magnet inserted through hole for crankcase-to-head tube</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Magnet inserted through back of crankcase</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert extension through exhaust pushrod hole for cylinder 7 and push torx bit into M6 x
                    40 torx bolt in block of branch tube assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat steps 45 through 47.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic07" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD13/D13138.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Removal of bolts from branch tube adaptor</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adaptor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two M6 x 30 bolts connecting branch tube adapter to branch tube assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651113" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD13/D13139.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removal of branch tube adapter</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">No.10 quick release tool</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adapter</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove branch tube adapter, using a No.10 Quick Release Tool .</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic08" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD13/D13140.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removal of O-ring</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove O-ring from recess in branch tube assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265ic09" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD13/D13144.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>High-pressure oil pump assembly and STC fitting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure oil pump assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Snap To Connection (STC) fitting</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove STC fitting.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove branch tube assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
